WEBVTT

00:05.255 --> 00:06.755
SARAH [VOICE-OVER]:
There are those who believe...

00:06.923 --> 00:09.925
...that a child in the womb
shares his mother's dreams.

00:10.468 --> 00:13.846
Her love for him,
her hopes for his future.

00:14.014 --> 00:17.266
Is it told to him in pictures
while he sleeps inside her?

00:17.434 --> 00:21.270
Is that why he reaches for her in that
first moment and cries for her touch?

00:22.272 --> 00:26.275
But what if you've known since he was
inside you what his life held for him.

00:26.443 --> 00:30.320
That he would be hunted, that his fate
was tied to the fate of millions...

00:30.488 --> 00:34.241
...that every moment of your life
would be spent keeping him alive?

00:34.409 --> 00:37.036
Would he understand
why you were so hard?

00:37.203 --> 00:40.831
Why you held on so tight?
Would he still reach for you...

00:40.999 --> 00:44.501
...if the only dream you've ever shared
with him was a nightmare?

00:48.965 --> 00:52.217
Would he know my love
runs through him like blood?

00:53.678 --> 00:54.845
John, now.

00:55.805 --> 00:57.431
Now.

01:03.146 --> 01:06.899
-The cops make you at the diner?
-I don't know. Maybe.

01:11.029 --> 01:13.155
Yes, definitely.

01:13.907 --> 01:15.574
COP 1 [OVER LOUDSPEAKER]:
Sarah Connor, John Connor.

01:16.159 --> 01:17.868
Drop what you're carrying.

01:18.036 --> 01:20.996
Put your hands on your head
and kneel on the ground.

01:21.748 --> 01:23.332
Now!

01:26.836 --> 01:28.253
[JOHN GRUNTS]

01:30.590 --> 01:32.049
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

01:36.471 --> 01:38.555
[DOGS BARKING IN DISTANCE]

01:48.233 --> 01:50.359
[ENGINE TURNS OVER AND STARTS]

01:56.116 --> 01:57.282
[RADIO CHATTER]

02:00.537 --> 02:02.287
Do me a favor, will you?

02:02.455 --> 02:04.081
Fix it.

02:06.126 --> 02:07.209
COP 2:
Ohhhh!

02:07.418 --> 02:09.294
[COP 2 GRUNTING]

02:09.879 --> 02:11.713
[COP 2 MOANING]

02:14.676 --> 02:16.385
[SIREN WAILING]

02:34.737 --> 02:36.405
COP 1:
Drop your weapon!

02:40.076 --> 02:41.410
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

02:49.836 --> 02:51.170
[SARAH GRUNTS]

02:51.421 --> 02:53.046
Move. Move.

02:53.923 --> 02:55.090
Get down.

03:05.059 --> 03:07.186
You run! Run!

03:26.164 --> 03:27.748
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

03:33.546 --> 03:35.422
John!

03:35.590 --> 03:37.299
John. John.

03:37.467 --> 03:46.266
John.

03:46.476 --> 03:48.185
No.

03:49.354 --> 03:51.188
Do it!

03:51.356 --> 03:54.399
Do it, kill me.
Nothing matters anymore.

03:55.818 --> 03:57.236
Kill me!

03:57.403 --> 03:59.404
You're right.

03:59.781 --> 04:01.823
Nothing matters anymore.

04:01.991 --> 04:03.575
Only the boy.

04:03.743 --> 04:05.285
The future's ours.

04:05.495 --> 04:08.664
And it begins now.

04:31.437 --> 04:32.896
[INHALES SHARPLY]

04:38.945 --> 04:40.237
Hey.

04:40.405 --> 04:42.781
Did you scream or something?

04:43.199 --> 04:45.242
Scream? No.

04:45.702 --> 04:47.035
[SIGHS]

04:49.080 --> 04:51.081
Go back to sleep.

04:51.416 --> 04:55.544
No, I can't. I've got early shift.

04:59.382 --> 05:01.091
Are you all right?

05:01.467 --> 05:02.801
I'm good.

05:02.969 --> 05:04.303
-Yeah?
-I'm great.

05:04.470 --> 05:07.055
Well, you damn well better be.

05:07.432 --> 05:11.268
You know the guy down at the store
told me any woman would be lucky...

05:11.686 --> 05:12.769
...to have this ring.

05:14.105 --> 05:16.773
He doesn't know the giver like I do.

05:21.279 --> 05:23.071
You wanna know a secret?

05:23.239 --> 05:25.240
I don't know. I don't like secrets.

05:25.408 --> 05:27.451
No? Ha, ha, this is a good one.

05:27.618 --> 05:29.578
-Really? Oh.
-Yeah.

05:29.912 --> 05:31.580
All right.

05:34.083 --> 05:35.459
John picked it out.

05:35.626 --> 05:37.085
Yeah, well, sort of.

05:38.129 --> 05:41.923
I'd been looking and looking and
I kind of started freaking myself out...

05:42.091 --> 05:44.593
...with the whole color and cut
and clarity--

05:44.761 --> 05:47.804
So you turned the job over
to a 15-year-old boy?

05:48.306 --> 05:50.724
You think I'm a jackass, don't you?

05:54.145 --> 05:56.313
Thinking I love you.

06:12.789 --> 06:15.165
Always remember that.

06:21.714 --> 06:22.798
Early shift.

06:24.634 --> 06:27.219
-Better get going.
-Right.

06:28.137 --> 06:29.930
Early shift. Uh-huh.

06:33.768 --> 06:35.268
Bye.

06:59.335 --> 07:00.419
[INHALES SHARPLY]

07:00.586 --> 07:04.339
Mom, how many times have I told you
it's freaky when you do that?

07:04.507 --> 07:05.966
I'm sorry.

07:08.177 --> 07:09.469
Mmm.

07:13.558 --> 07:14.766
What's going on?

07:20.064 --> 07:22.524
We can't stay here, John.

07:23.025 --> 07:24.484
What?

07:24.694 --> 07:25.902
It's not safe.

07:27.113 --> 07:29.156
Not safe from who?

07:29.323 --> 07:30.407
No one knows us.

07:30.575 --> 07:33.243
No one asks questions.
It's been almost two years.

07:33.411 --> 07:35.162
School starts in, like, three weeks.

07:35.329 --> 07:37.497
-We need to go.
-No, you need to go.

07:37.707 --> 07:40.167
You're scared. He gave you a ring
and now you freak out.

07:40.334 --> 07:42.711
-I know you like him.
-So do you, Mom.

07:43.296 --> 07:45.422
So do you.
You love him, I know you do.

07:46.757 --> 07:50.510
Listen to me,
the cops will never find us, we're safe.

07:51.345 --> 07:55.390
Don't you think that, John.
Don't you ever think that. Look at me.

07:55.558 --> 07:58.602
No one is ever safe.

08:06.736 --> 08:07.819
Half an hour.

08:09.030 --> 08:10.739
One bag...

08:10.907 --> 08:12.657
...plus the guns.

08:12.825 --> 08:14.743
I'll make pancakes.

08:27.089 --> 08:29.424
SARAH [VOICE-OVER]:
Every family has rules...

08:29.592 --> 08:31.051
...and we had ours.

08:31.260 --> 08:32.677
Keep your head down.

08:32.845 --> 08:34.095
Keep your eyes up.

08:34.263 --> 08:37.849
Resist the urge to be seen
as important or special.

08:40.394 --> 08:42.562
Know your exits.

08:45.691 --> 08:47.817
COP: I mean, she's not
exactly missing, right?

08:47.985 --> 08:49.486
-The way you explain it.
-Right.

08:49.654 --> 08:52.781
The way I explained it,
she's not missing, she left.

08:53.324 --> 08:56.243
-Happens more than you think.
-You don't know her.

08:56.410 --> 08:59.496
I could say the same to you,
Mr. Dixon.

09:01.374 --> 09:03.124
DIXON:
FBI?

09:03.543 --> 09:04.626
Been together long?

09:05.211 --> 09:07.712
Six months, maybe.
Bit of a whirlwind.

09:07.964 --> 09:10.799
Ha, ha, ha. You have no idea
the whirlwind.

09:10.967 --> 09:15.136
Tell me, does the Skynet
defense system mean anything to you?

09:17.640 --> 09:19.099
No.

09:19.559 --> 09:21.560
How about this guy?

09:21.894 --> 09:25.564
Miles Dyson. No.
Never seen him before.

09:25.898 --> 09:27.148
That's because he's dead.

09:28.359 --> 09:31.361
Your fiancée freshly escaped from the
Pescadero Mental Hospital...

09:31.529 --> 09:33.405
...blew him apart two years ago.

09:33.573 --> 09:35.740
Leveled a four-story research lab
along with him.

09:35.908 --> 09:39.578
But since there's no lethal injection
for the destruction of property...

09:39.745 --> 09:43.748
...let's just stick with the murder of one
of our brightest computer scientists...

09:45.042 --> 09:46.835
...and a dedicated family man.

09:48.421 --> 09:51.006
That's-- It's just not--

09:51.382 --> 09:53.675
Why would she do that, huh?

09:53.843 --> 09:56.177
Well, you know, Mr. Dixon.

09:56.345 --> 09:57.637
It's the robots.

10:00.016 --> 10:02.058
The ones from the future.

10:02.226 --> 10:04.936
The ones Skynet sent to kill her son?

10:05.855 --> 10:10.400
Which makes total sense, because in
the future, John's not only her son but--

10:10.568 --> 10:11.735
What does it say here?

10:11.902 --> 10:16.281
"The leader of the resistance
fighting artificially intelligent machines...

10:16.449 --> 10:19.242
...determined to annihilate
the human race."

10:21.662 --> 10:23.913
Did he strike you that way?

10:24.373 --> 10:27.626
Leader of a scrappy band of rebels?
Luke Skywalker type?

10:28.127 --> 10:29.878
He's just a kid.

10:30.046 --> 10:32.130
He's a great kid.
He was like a son to me.

10:36.302 --> 10:37.969
I came down here for help.

10:39.138 --> 10:40.805
You can't really be asking me this.

10:41.432 --> 10:44.184
No, I'm not.

10:44.393 --> 10:46.645
This is just my patter, Mr. Dixon.

10:47.104 --> 10:51.232
This is me impressing upon you that I'm
not here because you lost your fiancée.

10:51.400 --> 10:53.485
Love of your life and all around
good-time girl.

10:53.653 --> 10:56.237
I'm here because my boss,
the United States...

10:56.405 --> 10:59.824
...thinks Sarah Connor is a deluded,
dangerous, Grade A whack-a-mole...

10:59.992 --> 11:03.912
...who killed a man because she believes
in the future he'll invent a computer...

11:04.080 --> 11:06.247
...that declares war on the world.

11:06.457 --> 11:08.083
So let's begin with her name.

11:11.337 --> 11:12.796
I understand it's not Connor.

11:42.660 --> 11:44.661
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

12:02.847 --> 12:05.140
MAN 1: I couldn't go, so I saved it all
till the last minute.

12:05.307 --> 12:07.392
MAN 2: How'd it turn out?
MAN 1: Ah, I think all right.

12:07.643 --> 12:09.894
You'll be responsible
for three chapters a week.

12:10.104 --> 12:11.688
You have a quiz each Friday.

12:11.856 --> 12:14.566
You'll be allowed one makeup test
with a parent's note.

12:14.734 --> 12:18.236
-lf you're late for class without a note....
-What's your name?

12:18.404 --> 12:20.572
-John.
-Cameron.

12:20.740 --> 12:25.160
--cleaning beakers.
And no talking while I'm talking.

12:25.494 --> 12:27.537
[STUDENTS CHUCKLING]

12:32.126 --> 12:33.501
John?

12:33.669 --> 12:36.254
-Hey.
-I haven't seen you around here before.

12:36.422 --> 12:38.715
-Did you just move here?
-Yeah, I did.

12:38.883 --> 12:41.509
-Ha, ha. Sucks for you.
-Ha.

12:42.678 --> 12:44.262
My dad sells tractors.

12:44.430 --> 12:46.681
-What about yours?
-Insurance.

12:46.849 --> 12:48.183
Really? What kind?

12:49.769 --> 12:51.853
-The boring kind.
-Ha, ha, ha.

12:52.772 --> 12:55.190
Those are the kind of tractors
my dad sells.

12:55.357 --> 12:57.192
What about your mom?

12:57.902 --> 12:59.194
My mom stays home.

13:00.780 --> 13:04.199
You know, I've really gotta get
to the next class, so....

13:05.159 --> 13:08.536
So maybe I'll see you later?

13:09.663 --> 13:11.122
Sure, yeah.

13:11.290 --> 13:14.209
Okay, well, bye.

13:16.212 --> 13:17.962
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

13:24.303 --> 13:26.054
[CROWS CAWING]

13:31.060 --> 13:32.185
[DOOR OPENS]

13:43.447 --> 13:45.073
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING
ON HEADPHONES]

13:55.417 --> 13:56.751
[ROCK MUSIC STOPS]

13:56.919 --> 13:58.086
This is a hick town, Mom.

13:59.129 --> 14:01.130
We've been in worse places.

14:01.298 --> 14:02.924
A lot worse.

14:03.092 --> 14:04.926
Well, my clothes are all wrong.

14:05.094 --> 14:07.262
I need, like, some different shirts.

14:08.097 --> 14:11.140
You know, here everyone wears boots?
Like cowboy boots.

14:11.308 --> 14:12.809
I hate cowboy boots.

14:14.603 --> 14:16.104
See what I can do.

14:16.272 --> 14:19.357
Their computer's like from the frigging
'50s or something.

14:19.525 --> 14:24.529
-Their computers? I thought we agreed.
-No, they switched my class.

14:24.738 --> 14:28.783
-Last thing I need is you caught hacking.
-I'm not hacking. God, I know the rules.

14:28.951 --> 14:32.620
They're, like, written on the inside
of my eyeballs, all right?

14:35.958 --> 14:37.125
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

14:41.005 --> 14:46.050
[SIGHS]

14:47.261 --> 14:48.845
Hey.

14:55.269 --> 14:56.519
You meet any pretty girls?

14:56.687 --> 14:58.062
[JOHN SCOFFS]

14:58.981 --> 15:02.150
No. I'm telling you, it's a hick town.

15:09.283 --> 15:10.366
Come on.

15:29.178 --> 15:30.553
Agent Ellison.

15:31.055 --> 15:32.347
Welcome to New Mexico.

15:42.524 --> 15:46.027
The sheriff's detached me to hustle
you around on your business here.

15:46.195 --> 15:48.363
Whatever that is, he wouldn't say.

15:48.530 --> 15:50.365
He doesn't know.

15:53.118 --> 15:58.539
MAN [OVER PA]: --between Nutrition
and Second Period today.

15:58.707 --> 16:03.211
Come and show your support.
Show some pep.

16:06.548 --> 16:08.716
I lied to you yesterday.

16:09.718 --> 16:12.220
My dad doesn't sell insurance.

16:12.388 --> 16:14.055
He's dead.

16:15.057 --> 16:17.475
He was a soldier.
He was killed on a mission.

16:18.978 --> 16:21.312
-I'm sorry.
-Oh, it's all right.

16:21.480 --> 16:25.274
My mom was pregnant with me when
it happened. I never even knew him.

16:25.442 --> 16:26.943
So it's all right.

16:28.737 --> 16:31.739
My mom, she-- She's--
She's kind of uptight.

16:32.783 --> 16:35.827
Actually, no. She's really uptight.

16:35.995 --> 16:37.954
She likes me to come home
after school...

16:38.122 --> 16:40.123
...and hang out with her and that
kind of thing, you know?

16:40.290 --> 16:41.416
[INHALES SHARPLY]

16:41.583 --> 16:43.292
I'm all she's got.

16:48.007 --> 16:49.382
Thank you for explaining.

16:51.260 --> 16:53.636
It'll be our secret.

16:55.764 --> 16:57.640
[BELL RINGING]

17:02.646 --> 17:05.648
Mr. Ferguson is ill today.

17:06.650 --> 17:08.276
My name is Cromartie.

17:08.444 --> 17:10.778
Is that your only name, like Madonna?

17:11.447 --> 17:14.282
Madonna? Why? No.

17:14.950 --> 17:16.909
[STUDENTS LAUGHING]

17:22.666 --> 17:24.125
Let's take attendance, then.

17:25.461 --> 17:27.295
-Marie Booeye?
-Here.

17:28.922 --> 17:30.965
-Donald Chase.
-Here.

17:31.133 --> 17:33.676
-Franklin Lane.
-Here.

17:33.844 --> 17:37.138
-Cynthia Nolan.
-Here.

17:37.639 --> 17:40.516
-Wayne Parker.
-Here.

17:40.684 --> 17:42.810
Cameron Phillips.

17:44.688 --> 17:46.355
Cameron?

17:47.316 --> 17:48.816
Here.

17:50.486 --> 17:55.740
Reese.
Do we have a John Reese?

17:56.992 --> 17:58.493
[JOHN CLEARS THROAT]

17:59.828 --> 18:00.870
Excellent.

18:05.209 --> 18:06.667
[STUDENTS YELLING AND SCREAMING]

18:25.229 --> 18:26.979
[TERMINATOR'S LEG WHIRRING]

18:27.231 --> 18:29.524
Class dismissed.

19:10.649 --> 19:13.734
WOMAN [ON TV]: Witnesses are
reporting gunfire just minutes ago...

19:13.902 --> 19:17.029
...at Crestview High School
in Red Valley. Police are--

19:37.801 --> 19:39.135
[GRUNTS]

19:43.140 --> 19:44.473
Ahhh.

20:01.283 --> 20:02.783
Come with me if you wanna live.

20:41.823 --> 20:42.865
[GRUNTS]

20:46.954 --> 20:48.663
-Sarah Connor.
-Where is he?

20:49.831 --> 20:51.666
What have you done with him?

20:56.004 --> 20:57.713
You don't know.

20:57.881 --> 20:59.674
You don't know?

20:59.841 --> 21:02.051
Killing yourself is the best strategy.

21:02.219 --> 21:05.346
If you're alive,
I can use you against him.

21:06.014 --> 21:07.181
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

21:07.391 --> 21:08.516
[SARAH GAGGING]

21:11.520 --> 21:13.229
[IN SARAH'S VOICE] John?
-Mom, Mom.

21:13.397 --> 21:14.522
I tried to call you.

21:14.690 --> 21:16.023
JOHN [ON PHONE]:
I've been trying to call you.

21:16.191 --> 21:18.567
Listen to me, okay?
They're back. It's back.

21:18.735 --> 21:22.363
-John, slow down. Where are you?
JOHN: I'm going to the house.

21:22.531 --> 21:24.031
-I'll be right there.
-Mom.

21:24.199 --> 21:27.535
I love you, John. Stay right there.

21:33.000 --> 21:34.709
Let's go.

21:36.128 --> 21:37.378
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

21:42.009 --> 21:43.509
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

21:44.303 --> 21:45.636
[DOG BARKING]

21:53.895 --> 21:55.271
[GAGGING]

21:55.605 --> 21:56.772
[IN SARAH'S VOICE]
John?

21:59.651 --> 22:01.235
John.

22:04.948 --> 22:06.991
-Are you okay?
JOHN: Mom?

22:07.159 --> 22:08.451
-John?
JOHN: Mom?

22:10.620 --> 22:12.830
John! No!

22:13.040 --> 22:14.248
John!

22:14.541 --> 22:16.250
[SARAH EXHALES SHARPLY]

22:17.586 --> 22:19.253
CAMERON [IN JOHN'S VOICE]:
Neat trick. You like?

22:21.256 --> 22:22.340
[SARAH GRUNTING]

23:10.305 --> 23:13.057
Next time you do
what you're trained to do. You run.

23:13.225 --> 23:14.683
Go. Ugh.

23:34.162 --> 23:35.871
[ENGINE REWING]

23:43.713 --> 23:45.548
[BANGING]

23:48.635 --> 23:49.844
[JOHN GRUNTS]

23:53.640 --> 23:54.849
Did you stop him?

23:55.016 --> 23:57.893
One hundred twenty seconds
and the system reboots.

23:58.061 --> 24:01.647
-I was sent here to protect John.
-Not now. Not yet.

24:46.860 --> 24:49.361
You might want to put
those back in the holster.

24:50.363 --> 24:51.697
Oh.

24:54.701 --> 24:56.577
We should be good here
two more hours.

24:58.413 --> 25:00.789
Hit the border at lunchtime.

25:03.335 --> 25:04.752
What year are you from?

25:04.920 --> 25:06.337
2027.

25:09.674 --> 25:12.051
How long have you
been looking for us?

25:12.219 --> 25:13.719
Seventy-three days.

25:15.597 --> 25:16.722
And the war?

25:17.182 --> 25:21.685
The Skynet missile defense system
goes online April 19th, 2011.

25:21.853 --> 25:26.774
Declares war on mankind and triggers
a nuclear apocalypse two days later.

25:28.151 --> 25:30.152
And Miles Dyson?

25:30.320 --> 25:32.947
Someone else builds Skynet.

25:35.158 --> 25:36.617
Who?

25:37.285 --> 25:39.411
-We don't know.
-You don't know who builds...

25:39.621 --> 25:40.913
...the computer that
blows up the world?

25:41.122 --> 25:42.665
I wasn't sent here for that.

25:42.832 --> 25:46.544
No. You were sent here to keep
my son from being assassinated.

25:48.880 --> 25:50.714
Your fiancé went to the police.

25:51.841 --> 25:53.592
You should've changed your alias.

25:54.594 --> 25:56.387
Go to hell.

26:00.850 --> 26:02.309
They'd have found you anyway.

26:03.186 --> 26:05.104
They always do.

26:07.732 --> 26:09.400
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

26:20.829 --> 26:22.329
[CHATTERING ON RADIO]

26:30.046 --> 26:32.172
There's Kevlar in that chair.

26:32.340 --> 26:34.592
APB's statewide, but it's been--

26:34.759 --> 26:35.843
Nineteen hours.

26:39.139 --> 26:40.764
What the hell happened here?

26:42.183 --> 26:45.185
Twenty-two witnesses, Deputy Ridge.

26:46.354 --> 26:49.023
Twenty-two of your good town folk.

26:49.649 --> 26:51.859
That's a whole football team.

26:52.027 --> 26:53.652
Guess what 19 of them saw?

26:54.195 --> 27:00.743
A shooter
with some kind of robot leg.

27:01.286 --> 27:02.369
[SIGHS]

27:31.941 --> 27:33.067
Hey.

27:34.903 --> 27:36.612
Why is this happening again?

27:42.744 --> 27:44.495
I don't know.

27:45.205 --> 27:46.747
You stopped it.

27:48.625 --> 27:50.709
I guess I didn't.

27:57.258 --> 27:59.134
But you can.

28:02.097 --> 28:04.598
You changed the future,
you didn't change it enough.

28:04.766 --> 28:06.141
So you can do it again.

28:06.309 --> 28:10.270
-I don't know, John.
-I can't keep running. I can't.

28:12.524 --> 28:13.982
I'm not who they think I am.

28:14.150 --> 28:15.359
Some messiah.

28:15.527 --> 28:17.736
You don't know that.

28:20.115 --> 28:22.449
I know.

28:22.617 --> 28:24.535
I can't lead an army.

28:25.745 --> 28:29.498
Maybe that's you but it'll never be me,
so you've gotta stop it.

28:29.999 --> 28:31.542
Please.

28:36.464 --> 28:38.048
Mom.

28:41.970 --> 28:43.637
All right.

28:46.808 --> 28:48.183
All right, what?

28:51.813 --> 28:53.480
SARAH:
I'll stop it.

28:54.983 --> 28:56.900
I'll stop it.

29:04.325 --> 29:06.160
[BEEPING]

29:06.411 --> 29:08.370
We're not going across the border.

29:08.538 --> 29:10.497
Where are we going?

29:10.665 --> 29:12.583
To find Skynet.

29:25.889 --> 29:27.514
Chip?

29:38.234 --> 29:40.027
Back at school...

29:40.195 --> 29:42.070
...you apologized for lying to me.

29:42.238 --> 29:44.698
So I should apologize for lying to you.

29:48.703 --> 29:50.412
It's all right, I get it.

29:52.081 --> 29:55.209
You needed to get close to me.
It's just the way you're...

29:56.377 --> 29:58.128
...programmed.

29:59.923 --> 30:03.759
Like some hot girl is really gonna try and
make friends with the new weird kid.

30:05.094 --> 30:06.970
If I'd thought about it...

30:07.138 --> 30:10.224
...I would have known something
was messed up, you know?

30:13.770 --> 30:16.104
In the future, you have many friends.

30:22.737 --> 30:24.738
What model are you?

30:25.573 --> 30:27.950
Are you new? You seem...

30:29.285 --> 30:30.786
...different.

30:36.876 --> 30:38.627
I am.

30:46.636 --> 30:48.262
Let's go.

30:58.147 --> 30:59.273
[DOORBELL RINGS]

30:59.440 --> 31:02.025
Mom, pizza's here.

31:02.443 --> 31:04.903
Mom, the pizza.

31:08.491 --> 31:10.158
Mom?

31:11.202 --> 31:13.537
-You.
-We need to talk about Miles, Tarissa.

31:13.705 --> 31:16.999
Danny, go to your room. Right now.

31:17.625 --> 31:20.127
-How dare you come here?
-I know what they told you.

31:20.295 --> 31:23.338
-But it didn't happen that way.
-Get the hell out of here.

31:23.506 --> 31:25.632
-Now.
-It didn't happen that way.

31:29.804 --> 31:31.013
I can't let you do that.

31:31.180 --> 31:32.806
TARISSA: Let go!
-Listen to me.

31:33.808 --> 31:35.350
I didn't kill Miles.

31:35.518 --> 31:37.060
[TARISSA INHALES SHARPLY]

31:37.228 --> 31:39.313
All right? l didn't do it.

31:39.480 --> 31:40.939
[INHALES SHARPLY]

31:41.649 --> 31:43.317
I would never.

31:43.818 --> 31:45.819
Miles was a hero.

31:45.987 --> 31:47.738
Then why are you here?

31:48.948 --> 31:50.824
CAMERON:
We're back.

31:52.702 --> 31:54.161
[MACHINE WHIRRING]

31:57.957 --> 32:00.375
TARISSA: You told me
there'd be no more machines.

32:02.462 --> 32:03.503
[TARISSA SIGHS]

32:07.508 --> 32:11.011
Look, it's happening again.
Everything we fought to stop.

32:11.471 --> 32:13.847
Miles' work at Cyberdyne
is the only link we have.

32:14.015 --> 32:17.351
Is there anyone, anywhere
who's shown an interest in his work?

32:17.518 --> 32:20.520
Anyone he could have told,
someone he forgot?

32:20.688 --> 32:23.023
There's nobody. It's all gone.

32:23.191 --> 32:24.691
You destroyed it all.

32:24.859 --> 32:27.235
You and Miles destroyed--

32:27.403 --> 32:28.862
[INHALES SHARPLY]

32:29.864 --> 32:32.532
You destroyed everything.

32:34.869 --> 32:36.370
[FOOTSTEPS]

32:36.871 --> 32:38.246
We have to go.

32:38.790 --> 32:40.290
Now.

32:44.045 --> 32:45.712
[DOGS BARKING]

32:55.223 --> 32:57.015
Help me.

32:57.392 --> 32:59.142
Help my son.

33:05.149 --> 33:06.942
[CAR ENGINE STARTS]

33:08.903 --> 33:10.028
[ENGINE REWING]

33:10.238 --> 33:11.530
[TIRES SQUEALING]

33:22.333 --> 33:24.084
Mom! Mom!

33:27.922 --> 33:29.756
[TIRES SQUEALING]

33:33.469 --> 33:36.304
[BEEPING]

33:43.813 --> 33:45.480
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

33:46.983 --> 33:48.567
Oh, God.

34:03.624 --> 34:05.459
[TIRES SCREECHING]

34:06.294 --> 34:07.711
[BANGING]

34:10.923 --> 34:12.924
Bandages. Rubbing alcohol.

34:13.092 --> 34:14.885
-Mom, you need a doctor.
-Go!

34:15.053 --> 34:16.803
We'll find cover out back.

34:16.971 --> 34:19.056
First aid kit on the floor.

34:30.902 --> 34:32.986
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

34:38.993 --> 34:40.702
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

34:40.912 --> 34:43.455
Get it done before he gets back.

34:44.999 --> 34:48.335
I'll get some ice.
It'll numb you, slow the blood loss.

34:48.503 --> 34:50.754
Needle and thread
slow the blood loss.

34:50.922 --> 34:52.005
Do it now.

34:54.842 --> 34:59.596
[SARAH EXHALES SHARPLY]

35:04.352 --> 35:06.311
[CLOTHES RIPPING]

35:15.863 --> 35:18.240
We can't keep running.

35:21.244 --> 35:23.620
I'll lose my boy.

35:26.791 --> 35:34.631
He'll leave me.

35:56.696 --> 35:59.322
-What time is it?
-7:52.

36:00.032 --> 36:01.741
How's the arm?

36:01.909 --> 36:04.536
-Better.
CAMERON: Good.

36:04.704 --> 36:07.080
-We need to go.
-Where?

36:09.041 --> 36:10.584
I'll show you.

36:17.049 --> 36:19.050
Do you have, like, an account here?

36:19.218 --> 36:20.677
Safety deposit box.

36:20.845 --> 36:22.179
When did you open that?

36:22.346 --> 36:24.764
1 963.

36:28.019 --> 36:29.686
[CHATTERING]

36:32.607 --> 36:33.732
Everybody on the floor.

36:34.317 --> 36:35.817
Please.

36:36.444 --> 36:37.611
[ALL CHATTERING LOUDLY]

36:43.910 --> 36:45.619
Keys to the safety deposit boxes.

36:46.913 --> 36:48.622
[GUN COCKS]

36:54.837 --> 36:57.380
Get inside. Keys.

37:01.761 --> 37:04.137
Lock us in
and then get away from the door.

37:04.347 --> 37:05.764
I'll know if you don't.

37:19.153 --> 37:21.988
You said you had a safety
deposit box.

37:23.157 --> 37:24.616
I do.

37:47.348 --> 37:49.432
Open these boxes.

37:49.600 --> 37:51.851
Put everything you find on the table.

37:52.979 --> 37:54.521
Carefully.

38:22.883 --> 38:24.634
[TIRES SCREECHING]

38:31.851 --> 38:34.728
Hey, James. You gotta see this.

38:38.566 --> 38:40.984
The alarm tripped seven minutes ago.

38:41.152 --> 38:44.654
Camera autodumps a digital copy
to the L.A.P.D. servers.

38:44.822 --> 38:46.156
Don't you know them?

38:47.950 --> 38:50.243
Less and less all the time.

38:52.330 --> 38:54.414
Is that from the future?

38:54.582 --> 38:56.875
You can't bring anything through
when you come.

38:57.043 --> 38:59.002
Not weapons, not clothing...

38:59.170 --> 39:00.712
...nothing.

39:03.049 --> 39:05.759
You send someone back to build it.

39:08.512 --> 39:10.096
What is it?

39:10.264 --> 39:11.765
Hope.

39:15.978 --> 39:17.729
[TIRES SCREECHING]

39:25.613 --> 39:27.906
[MACHINE WHIRRING]

39:39.794 --> 39:41.628
Is that the police?

39:41.796 --> 39:43.755
-No. Get away from the door.
-Why?

39:46.300 --> 39:47.509
That's why.

40:02.316 --> 40:05.819
-That better be what I think it is.
CAMERON: One of our best engineers.

40:05.986 --> 40:08.780
Took him eight months
to scavenge the parts.

40:08.948 --> 40:11.157
When the isotope solution turns red,
you fire.

40:11.325 --> 40:13.159
Isotope?

40:13.327 --> 40:14.577
What, is this nuclear?

40:14.745 --> 40:16.121
No, not really.

40:21.168 --> 40:22.544
[CRASHING]

40:23.421 --> 40:24.796
I don't get why you locked it.

40:24.964 --> 40:28.425
-We didn't have to get trapped.
-You're not trapped.

40:36.684 --> 40:38.184
What is that?

40:38.352 --> 40:40.270
Engineer got a job building the vault.

40:40.438 --> 40:42.480
So we'd always have a way
back home.

40:44.442 --> 40:45.775
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

40:48.154 --> 40:49.529
[BANGING]

40:54.702 --> 40:57.620
-What have you done?
-You wanna find Skynet?

40:57.788 --> 40:59.038
You wanna stop Skynet?

41:00.291 --> 41:02.792
-This is the way.
-You don't know who builds it.

41:02.960 --> 41:05.170
No. But we know where
and we know when.

41:05.337 --> 41:07.172
We can go kill it before it's born.

41:07.339 --> 41:10.967
You can stop running,
stay in one place, fight.

41:11.135 --> 41:13.553
[BANGING AND CRASHING]

41:32.823 --> 41:35.200
[BANGING]

41:37.745 --> 41:40.205
Mom, we gotta go, now.

41:45.419 --> 41:47.045
Mom!

41:49.882 --> 41:51.758
Do it!

42:02.269 --> 42:03.561
[SARAH GRUNTS]

42:12.696 --> 42:14.197
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

42:21.747 --> 42:28.253
[TIRES SQUEALING]

42:41.100 --> 42:43.184
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

43:19.430 --> 43:24.475
-Where are we?
-Same where. Different when.

43:37.323 --> 43:39.866
MAN 1:
Man, check this out.

43:40.034 --> 43:41.534
MAN 2: Oh, yeah.
MAN 3: Oh, yeah.

43:41.744 --> 43:43.202
MAN 4:
It'll be a good day, baby.

43:43.370 --> 43:44.787
I got something for you.

43:46.665 --> 43:48.207
[MEN GRUNTING]

44:00.387 --> 44:02.847
So, this is where it all starts?

44:04.266 --> 44:05.850
This is where Skynet begins?

44:07.269 --> 44:09.562
Somewhere in there.

44:10.689 --> 44:12.899
And nobody knows we're here?

44:23.786 --> 44:25.495
You're safe.

44:28.082 --> 44:30.333
-No one is ever safe.
-No one is ever safe.

44:39.426 --> 44:41.052
Come on.

44:50.604 --> 44:53.398
SARAH [VOICE-OVER]: It is said
that the death of any one person...

44:53.565 --> 44:55.608
...is the death of an entire world.

44:55.818 --> 44:57.777
Certainly for parents...

44:57.945 --> 45:00.697
...the death of a child
is no less than a holocaust.

45:00.864 --> 45:05.076
In the case of my son,
these words are literally true.

45:05.244 --> 45:06.619
MAN [ON TV]:
And finally tonight...

45:06.829 --> 45:08.621
...amateur video
of what we can only assume...

45:08.831 --> 45:10.748
...is a college prank gone wrong...

45:10.916 --> 45:15.044
...as three streakers caused chaos
trying to cross the 105 Freeway.

45:15.212 --> 45:17.922
Honey, did you hear me? We're late.

45:18.090 --> 45:21.259
Yeah, I heard you.

45:21.969 --> 45:24.262
SARAH [VOICE-OVER]: And even though
we've traveled through time...

45:24.430 --> 45:26.889
...bent the rules of nature...

45:28.058 --> 45:29.976
...they will keep coming for him...

45:30.144 --> 45:32.478
...keep trying to kill him.

45:33.105 --> 45:35.273
But until that day...

45:41.155 --> 45:44.157
...it's gonna be one hell of a dogfight.
